marginal, and conditional. The conditional mass function is the quotient of \
the joint mass function and the marginal mass function of the random variable \
being conditioned on.\n\tThe concept of independence also carries over \
readily to two or more discrete random variables.  In the case of two \
discrete random variables ",
 StyleBox["X",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["Y",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ", we say that they are ",
 StyleBox["independent",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " of each other if and only if for all subsets ",
 StyleBox["A",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " and ",
 StyleBox["B",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 " of their respective state spaces,"
}], "Text",
